(5:22)

which leads to the mass relation:

M 2P \Lambda 0 + M 2P = M 2P 01 + M 2P \Lambda : (5:23) This relation implies universal mass-squared splittings within the heavy meson doublets belonging to the lowest-lying quartet. Note also that in the ^m24 ! 0 limit there is complete degeneracy. Of course, our conclusions are general and apply to all heavy meson states. We conclude that the zero-helicity states of heavy mesons form reducible chiral quartets labelled by the light quark spin; generalizing Eq. (5.3) and Eq. (5.4) yields:

